qas.question: What two political parties dominate Portugal's government?

answers.text: Socialist Party and the Social Democratic Party

qas.question: At what three levels does the Portugal government operate?
What other political groups exist other than the two dominant ones?

answers.text: Unitary Democratic Coalition (Portuguese Communist Party and Ecologist Party "The Greens"), the Left Bloc and the Democratic and Social Centre – People's Party

qas.question: What percentage of the vote do the non-dominant parties get?

context: Portugal operates a multi-party system of competitive legislatures/local administrative governments at the <a1_0>national-, regional- and local-levels<a1_0/>. The Assembly of the Republic, Regional Assemblies and local municipalities and parishes, are dominated by two political parties, the <a0_0>Socialist Party and the Social Democratic Party<a0_0/>, in addition to the <a2_0>Unitary Democratic Coalition (Portuguese Communist Party and Ecologist Party "The Greens"), the Left Bloc and the Democratic and Social Centre – People's Party<a2_0/>, which garner between <a3_0>5 and 15%<a3_0/> of the vote regularly.
